ay: The Dazzler |url=https://www.surfer.com/blogs/eos/arnaud-de-rosnay-was-the-most-glamorous-surfer-of-all-time/ |accessdate=3 April 2020 |work=[[Surfer (magazine)|Surfer Magazine]] |date=22 December 2016}}</ref>\n*''[[Ritter|Frau]]'' [[Bette Midler|Martin Rochus Sebastian von Haselberg]] (''n\u00e9e'' Bette Midler) on 16 December 1984<ref>{{cite news |last1=Marino |first1=Vivian |title=Bette Midler\u2019s Fifth Avenue Penthouse Goes on the Market for $50 Million |url=https://www.nytimes.com/2019/09/06/realestate/bette-midlers-fifth-avenue-penthouse-goes-on-the-market-for-50-million.html?searchResultPosition=1 |accessdate=3 April 2020 |work=[[The New York Times]] |date=6 September 2019}}</ref><ref>{{cite news |last1=Losgar |first1=Maxwell |title=Hello, Sophie: Bette Midler\u2019s Daughter Is Ready For Her Close-Up |url=https://www.vanityfair.com/hollywood/2017/05/sophie-von-haselberg-bette-midler-bernie-madoff |accessdate=3 April 2020 |work=[[Vanity Fair (magazine)|Vanity Fair]] |language=en}}</ref>\n*[[Jamie Lee Curtis|Jamie Haden-Guest]], Baroness Haden-Guest (''n\u00e9e'' Jamie Lee Curtis) on 18 December 1984<ref>{{cite news |last1=Shattuck |first1=Kathryn |title=Christopher Guest: No Eccentric Obsession Left Behind |url=https://www.nytimes.com/2016/10/23/movies/snapshot-christopher-guest-mascots.html?searchResultPosition=1 |accessdate=3 April 2020 |work=[[The New York Times]] |date=21 October 2016}}</ref>\n*[[Laura Harring|Countess Carl-Eduard von Bismarck-Sch\u00f6nhausen]] (''n\u00e9e'' Laura Elena Herring Mart\u00ednez, aka Laura Harring) on 27 February 1987<ref>{{cite news |last1=Alexander |first1=Harriet |title=Bismarck heir sued in New York for $2.5m in child support |url=https://www.telegraph.co.uk/news/worldnews/northamerica/usa/12160202/Bismarck-heir-sued-in-New-York-for-2.5m-in-child-support.html |accessdate=3 April 2020 |work=Telegraph |date=16 February 2016}}</ref>\n*[[Inez Storer|Princess Andrew Romanov]] (''n\u00e9e'' Inez Bachelin, previously Sto