il 2020 |work=[[San Francisco Chronicle]] |date=15 May 2015}}</ref>\n*[[Aubrey Buxton, Baron Buxton of Alsa#Personal life|Kathleen Buxton]], Baroness Buxton of Alsa (''n\u00e9e'' Kathleen Peterson) on 16 July 1988<ref>{{cite news |last1=Purser |first1=Philip |title=Obituary {{!}} TV executive and naturalist {{!}} Lord Buxton of Alsa |url=https://www.theguardian.com/culture/2009/sep/07/lord-buxton-obituary |accessdate=3 April 2020 |work=The Guardian |date=7 September 2009}}</ref>\n*[[LuAnn de Lesseps|Countess Alexandre de Lesseps]] (''n\u00e9e'' LuAnn Nadeau, aka LuAnn de Lesseps) on 16 March 1993<ref>{{cite news |last1=Siegler |first1=Mara |title=Luann\u2019s ex-husband: \u2018She\u2019s ruining the family name\u2019 |url=https://pagesix.com/2017/12/29/luanns-ex-husband-shes-ruining-the-family-name/ |accessdate=3 April 2020 |work=[[Page Six]] |date=30 December 2017 |language=en}}</ref>\n*[[Stefanie Powers|Countess Patrick Houitte de la Chesnais]] (''n\u00e9e'' Stefanie Zofya Paul, aka Stefanie Powers, previously [[Gary Lockwood|Lockwood]]) on 1 April 1993<ref>{{cite news |last1=Paton |first1=Maureen |title=Stefanie Powers at 73: 'Everybody should get a medal at a certain point for surviving' |url=https://www.telegraph.co.uk/women/life/stefanie-powers-at-73-if-youve-lived-enough-years-its-inevitable/ |accessdate=3 April 2020 |work=The Telegraph |date=27 August 2016}}</ref>\n*Princess [[Prince Alexander-Georg von Auersperg|Alexander-Georg von Auersperg]] (''n\u00e9e'' Nancy Louise Weinberg) on 10 June 1995<ref>{{cite news |title=Notorious Still |url=https://people.com/archive/notorious-still-vol-54-no-25/ |accessdate=3 April 2020 |work=[[PEOPLE.com]] |language=EN}}</ref>\n*[[Marie-Chantal, Crown Princess of Greece]] (''n\u00e9e'' Marie-Chantal Miller) on 1 July 1995<ref>{{cite news |last1=Wilkinson |first1=Isabel |title=How Crown Princess Marie-Chantal of Greece Spends Her Sundays |url=https://www.nytimes.com/2020/03/20/nyregion/crown-princess-marie-chantal-greece.html?searchResultPosition=1 |accessdate=3 April 2020 |work=[[The New York Times]] |date=20 March 2020}}</ref>\n*[[Alexandra von Furstenberg|Princess Alexander von F\u00fcrstenberg]] (''n\u00e9e'' Alexandra Natasha Miller) on 28 October 1995<ref>{{cite news |last1=Goldberg |first1=Carey |title=Quiet High-Society Wedding Is a Spectacle for Gawkers |url=https://www.nytimes.com/1995/10/29/nyregion/quiet-high-society-wedding-is-a-spectacle-for-gawkers.html |accessdate=3 April 2020 |date=October 29, 1995}}</ref>\n*Princess [[Paul-Philippe Hohenzollern|Paul-Philippe von Hohenzollern]] (''n\u00e9e'' Lia Georgia Triff, previously [[Melvin Belli|Belli]]) on 15 September 1996<ref>{{cite news |last1=Simpson |first1=Daniel |title=Bucharest Journal; The King's Heir? Hmm, That's Not Fully Apparent |url=https://www.nytimes.com/2002/06/19/international/europe/19BUCH.html |accessdate=3 April 2020 |work=[[The New York Times]] |date=19 June 2002}}</ref>\n\n==Fictional American heiresses==\n*[[Alexis Colby]], [[Fallon Carrington Colby]], [[Amanda Carrington]], [[Krystle Carrington]] and [[Dominique Deveraux]] on the TV series ''[[Dynasty (1981 TV series)|Dynasty]]''\n*[[Pam Ewing]], [[April Stevens Ewing]], [[Ann Ewing (Dallas)|Ann Ewing]], [[Sue Ellen Ewing]], [[Valene Ewing]] and [[Lucy Ewing]] on the TV series ''[[Dallas (1978 TV series)|Dallas]]''\n*[[Angela Channing (Falcon Crest)|Angela Channing]] (portrayed by [[Jane Wyman]]) in the primetime television soap opera ''[[Falcon Crest]]''\n*[[Sue Ellen Mischke]] (portrayed by [[Brenda Strong]]) in the [[sitcom]] ''[[Seinfeld]]''\n*Mary Beth, Andrew Van de Kamp's friend (portrayed by [[Ashley Austin Morris]]) on the television series ''[[Desperate Housewives]]''\n*[[Stephanie Forrester (The Bold and the Beautiful)|Stephanie Forrester]], [[Pamela Douglas]], [[Felicia Forrester]], [[Steffy Forrester]], [[Phoebe Forrester]], [[Brooke Logan]], [[Taylor Forrester]], [[Darla Forrester]], [[Caroline Spencer]] and [[Caroline Spencer Forrester]] 