tesonline/>\n|-\n|St. Aloysius Church and Chancery\n|[[File:Detroit Washington Blvd.jpg|100px]]\n|1924<br/>1930\n|1234 Washington Boulevard, Detroit <br/><small>{{coord|42|19|58|N|83|3|3|W|name=St. Aloysious Roman Catholic Church Complex}}</small>\n|Romanesque Revival\n|Donaldson and Meier\n|Part of the [[Washington Boulevard Historic District]] listed on the [[National Register of Historic Places]]<ref name=NationalRegisterWayne/> and as a [[Michigan State Historic Preservation Office|Michigan Historic Site]].<ref name=sitesonline/> Chancery sold in 2015 and offices relocated.<ref name=move>{{cite news| title=New Chancery, new beginning: Better to serve| url=http://www.themichigancatholic.org/2015/02/new-chancery-new-beginning-better-to-serve/| work=The Michigan Catholic| date=February 20, 2015| accessdate=2016-03-16}}</ref> \n|-\n|St. Anthony Cathedral Abbey Roman Catholic Church\n|[[File:St Anthony Church.JPG|100px]]\n|1901\n|5247 Sheridan Street, Detroit\n|Romanesque Revival\n|Donaldson and Meier\n|Listed as a [[Michigan State Historic Preservation Office|Michigan Historic Site]].<ref name=sitesonline/>\n|-\n|[[Ste. Anne de Detroit Catholic Church]]\n|[[File:St Anne's Church.jpg|100px]]\n|1886\n| 1000 Ste. Anne Street, Detroit <br/><small>{{coord|42|19|14.83|N|83|4|16.16|W|name=Ste. Anne de Detroit Catholic Church}}</small>\n|Classical Revival, Late Gothic Revival\n|Leon Coquard\n| Listed on the [[National Register of Historic Places]]<ref name=NationalRegisterWayne/> and as a [[Michigan State Historic Preservation Office|Michigan Historic Site]].<ref name=sitesonline/>\n|-\n|[[St. Bonaventure Monastery]]\n|[[File:Saint Bonaventure Monastery 1.jpg|100px]]\n|1883\n|1740 Mt. Elliott, Detroit<br/><small>{{coord|42|21|4|N|83|0|52|W|name=St. Bonaventure Monastery}}</small>\n|[[Gothic Revival architecture|Gothic Revival]]\n|Peter J. Diederichs\n|Listed on the [[National Register of Historic Places]]<ref name=NationalRegisterWayne/> and as a [[Michigan State Historic P