ee & Associates\n|\n|-\n|[[St. Josaphat Roman Catholic Church]]\n|[[File:StJosephats.jpg|100px]]\n|1901\n|715 E. Canfield Avenue, Detroit<br/><small>{{coord|42|21|21|N|83|3|10|W|name=St. Josaphat's Roman Catholic Church}}</small>\n|Romanesque Revival\n|Joseph G. Kastler, William E. N. Hunter\n|Listed on the [[National Register of Historic Places]]<ref name=NationalRegisterWayne/> and as a [[Michigan State Historic Preservation Office|Michigan Historic Site]].<ref name=sitesonline/>\n|-\n|[[St. Joseph Roman Catholic Church, Detroit|St. Joseph Roman Catholic Church]]\n|[[File:StJosephsRCC.jpg|100px]]\n|1870\n|1828 Jay Street, Detroit<br/><small>{{coord|42|20|43|N|83|2|8|W|name=St. Joseph Roman Catholic Church}}</small>\n|Late Gothic Revival; German [[Hall church|Hall Church]]\n|Francis G. Himpler; [[Donaldson and Meier]]\n|St. Joseph's is an authentic German parish noted for its architecture and stained glass. Listed on the [[National Register of Historic Places]]<ref name=NationalRegisterWayne/> and as a [[Michigan State Historic Preservation Office|Michigan Historic Site]].<ref name=sitesonline/>\n|-\n|[[St. Mary Roman Catholic Church (Detroit, Michigan)|St. Mary Roman Catholic Church]]\n|[[File:StMarysGreektownDetroit.jpg|100px]]\n|1875\n|646 Monroe Street, Detroit<br/><small>{{coord|42|20|9|N|83|2|26|W|name=Old St. Mary's Roman Catholic Church}}</small>\n|Romanesque Revival\n|Peter J. Dederichs\n|Listed as a [[Michigan State Historic Preservation Office|Michigan Historic Site]].<ref name=sitesonline/>\n|-\n|[[Saints Peter and Paul Church, Detroit, Michigan|Saints Peter and Paul Church]]\n|[[File:Saints Peter and Paul Church Detroit MI.jpg|100px]]\n|1848\n|629 E. Jefferson Avenue, Detroit<br/><small>{{coord|42|19|55|N|83|2|18|W|name=Saints Peter and Paul Church}}</small>\n|Romanesque Revival\n|Francis Letouneau, Peter Kindenkins\n|Listed on the [[National Register of Historic Places]]<ref name=NationalRegisterWayne/> and as a [[Michigan State Historic Preservation 