 de Milo'' [Version 2]{{ref label|Rav_Bib_z|z|}}\n| in ''M\u00e9moires de l'Acad\u00e9mie des Insciptions et Belle-Lettres, vol. XXXIV, Part 1, 1892, pp. 145-256.<br/>also pub. as off-prints by Klincksieck: Paris, 1892 \n| \"Venus de Milo\" [Part]{{ref label|Rav_Bib_aa|aa|}}\n| Trans. M Sinclair: ''F\u00e9lix Ravaisson: Selected Essays'', 2016, pp. 189-228.\n|-\n\n| 1893\n| \"M\u00e9taphysique et morale\"\n| Revue de m\u00e9taphysique et morale 1, 1893, 6\u201325\n| \"Metaphysics and Morals\"\n| translated by Mark Sinclair in Ravaisson, Selected Essays, 279\u201394.\n|-\n\n| 1901\n| \"Testament philosophique\"\n| first edited and published by Xavier L\u00e9on in Revue de m\u00e9taphysique et de morale 9/1 (1901) 1\u201331 from notes left after his death\n| \n| \n|-\n\n| 1933\n| ''Testament philosophique''\n| expanded version by Charles Devivaise \n| ''Philosophical Testament''\n| translated by J. Dunham and M. Sinclair in Ravaisson, Selected Essays, 295\u2013336\n|-\n\n| colspan=\"5\" style=\"text-align:left; font-size:10pt;\"| Notes<br />\n{{refbegin}}\n\n* '''a''' {{Note|Rav_Bib_a}} Sinclair in ''Being Inclined'': 'In 1834' when 21 years of age, Ravaisson 'was the remarkably young laureate of a competition organized by the ''Acad\u00e9mie des sciences morales et politiques'' on Aristotle's ''Metaphysics'' and its historical reception, with a dissertation - ''De la M\u00e9taphysique d\u2019Aristote'' - that he would later publish in a revised and expanded form as ''Essai sur la M\u00e9taphysique d\u2019Aristote'' [Volume 1] (1837).<ref name=\"SinclairBI-7\">\"Sinclair (2019), p. 7</ref> See also Sinclair 'Introduction' in ''F\u00e9lix Ravaisson: Selected Essays''.<ref name=\"SinclairI-2-3\">\"Sinclair (2016), pp. 2-3</ref>\n* '''b''' {{Note|Rav_Bib_a}} Sinclair in ''Being Inclined'': 'Long sections of' ''De la M\u00e9taphysique d\u2019Aristote'' 'with the original pagination in the margins, are published in R. Belay and C. Marin, ''De la nature \u00e0 l\u2019esprit'' (Paris: ENS Editions, 2001), 201\u201313.'<ref name=\"SinclairBI-xi\">\"Sinclair (2019), p. xi</ref>\n* '''c''' {{Note|Rav_Bib_c}} Revised and expanded version of Ravaisson's 1834 prize winning essay ''De la M\u00e9taphysique d\u2019Aristote''.<ref name=\"SinclairBI-7\">\"Sinclair (2019), p. 7</ref>\n* '''d''' {{Note|Rav_Bib_d}} See Sinclair in ''Being Inclined''.<ref name=\"SinclairBI-6\">\"Sinclair (2019), p. 6</ref>\n* '''e''' {{Note|Rav_Bib_e}} See Sinclair in ''Being Inclined''.<ref name=\"SinclairBI-xi\">\"Sinclair (2019), p. xi</ref>\n* '''f''' {{Note|Rav_Bib_f}} See Sinclair's ''F\u00e9lix Ravaisson: Selected Essays''.<ref name=\"SinclairI-vi\">\"Sinclair (2016), p. vi</ref>\n* '''g''' {{Note|Rav_Bib_g}} As well as translating the text, Carlisle and Sinclair also included two extensive supplements by way of an \"Editors\u2019 Introduction\" and \"Editors\u2019 Commentary\".<ref name=\"Carlisle&Sinclair-1-21&78-114\">\"Carlisle & Sinclair (2008), pp. 1-21; 78-114</ref> In addition, there is a long preface from Catherine Malabou titled \"Addiction and Grace\".\n* '''h''' {{Note|Rav_Bib_h}} This publication is a bilingual edition of the text and presents both ''De l\u2019habitude'' and the translation by Carlisle and Sinclair (''Of Habit'') on facing pages of the book. The French version is the Alcan edition of 1933.<ref name=\"Carlisle&Sinclair-20\">\"Carlisle & Sinclair (2008), p. 20</ref>\n* '''i''' {{Note|Rav_Bib_i}} Sinclair writes that the translation has been modified since the original translation by Carlisle and himself a few years earlier in F\u00e9lix Ravaisson ''Of Habit'' (London/New York: Continuum, 2008).<ref name=\"SinclairI-vi\">\"Sinclair (2016), p. vi</ref>\n* '''j''' {{Note|Rav_Bib_j}} See Sinclair in ''Being Inclined''.<ref name=\"SinclairBI-6\">\"Sinclair (2019), p. 6</ref>\n* '''k''' {{Note|Rav_Bib_k}} Translated as ''La doctrine de Speusippe sur les premiers principes selon le t\u00e9moignage d'Aristote'' in ''Cahiers Philosophiques'' (n\u00b0129, 2\u00e8me trimestre), 2012; pp. 68\u201396. Translation by Alain Petit, preceded by an introduction from Petit titled \"Le sympt\u00f4me Speusippe: le spectre de l\u2019\u00e9manatisme dans la pens\u00e9e m\u00e9taphysique de Ravaisson\" (2012).<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.cairn.info/revue-cahiers-philosophiques1-2012-2-page-68.htm#|title=Ravaisson, la doctrine de Speusippe sur les premiers principes selon le t\u00e9moignage d'Aristote|publisher=Cahiers Philosophiques|date=2012|accessdate=2020-04-05}}</ref>\n* '''l''' {{Note|Rav_Bib_l}} See also Sinclair's commentary in \"Introduction\" in ''F\u00e9lix Ravaisson: Selected Essays''.<ref name=\"SinclairI-8-9\">\"Sinclair (2016), pp. 8-9</ref>\n* '''m''' {{Note|Rav_Bib_m}} See Sinclair's commentary in \"Introduction\" in ''F\u00e9lix Ravaisson: Selected Essays''.<ref name=\"SinclairI-3-4\">\"Sinclair (2016), pp. 3-4</ref> Sinclair points out that this second volume developed (but did not repeat) work from his 1834 prize winning essay ''De la M\u00e9taphysique d\u2019Aristote'' (1834) which had been revised and expanded in volume one (1837). Sinclair also mentions that a third and fourth volume were planned, but never came to fruition. In a footnote, however, Sinclair continues that Charles Devivaise 'published some of Ravaisson's work towards the third volume as ''Essai sur la Metaphysique d'Aristote: Fragments du Tome III'' (Paris: Vrin, 1953)'.<ref name=\"SinclairI-25\">\"Sinclair (2016), p. 25</ref> \n* '''n''' {{Note|Rav_Bib_n}} This published text originally appeared as \"Rapport address\u00e9 \u00e0 M. le ministre de l\u2019Instruction publique et des cultes\" (28 December 1853).<ref name=\"SinclairI-vi\">\"Sinclair (2016), p. vi</ref> See Sinclair's commentary in \"Introduction\" in ''F\u00e9lix Ravaisson: Selected Essays''.<ref name=\"SinclairI-11-12\">\"Sinclair (2016), pp. 11-12</ref> \n* '''o''' {{Note|Rav_Bib_o}} This translation is of the first 'untitled' segment of the text.<ref name=\"SinclairI-vi\">\"Sinclair (2016), p. vi</ref> In a footnote, Sinclair writes: 'For reasons of economy, I follow Dominique Janicaud in ''L'Art et les myst\u00e8res grecs'' (Paris: L'Herne, 1985) in producing just the first section of the report, but I alter his title ''L'Art et le dessin d'apr\u00e8s L\u00e9onard da Vinci''.'<ref name=\"SinclairI-27\">\"Sinclair (2016), p. 27</ref>\n* '''p''' {{Note|Rav_Bib_p}} Original version presented as a paper to the Acad\u00e9mie des Insciptions et Belle-Lettres in 1849 then 1851; this version extended for publication. See Sinclair's commentary in \"Introduction\" in ''F\u00e9lix Ravaisson: Selected Essays''.<ref name=\"SinclairI-10-11\">\"Sinclair (2016), pp. 10-11</ref> Published in 1856 with a cover date of 1877.<ref name=\"SinclairI-vi\">\"Sinclair (2016), p. vi</ref><ref name=\"SinclairI-11\">\"Sinclair (2016), p. 11</ref>\n* '''q''' {{Note|Rav_Bib_q}} See Sinclair's commentary in \"Introduction\" in ''F\u00e9lix Ravaisson: Selected Essays''.<ref name=\"SinclairI-13-15\">\"Sinclair (2016), pp. 13-15</ref>\n* '''r''' {{Note|Rav_Bib_r}} The first of two versions, the second reworked edition published in 1892. See Sinclair's commentary in \"Introduction\" in ''F\u00e9lix Ravaisson: Selected Essays''.<ref name=\"SinclairI-15-18\">\"Sinclair (2016), pp. 15-18</ref>\n* '''s''' {{Note|Rav_Bib_s}} Publication details.<ref name=\"SinclairI-28\">\"Sinclair (2016), p. 28</ref>\n* '''t''' {{Note|Rav_Bib_t}} Originally written in 1854, and not published for 20 years. See Sinclair's commentary in \"Introduction\" in ''F\u00e9lix Ravaisson: Selected Essays''.<ref name=\"SinclairI-12-13\">\"Sinclair (2016), pp. 12-13</ref> Sinclair also has a footnote with further details.<ref name=\"SinclairI-27\">\"Sinclair (2016), p. 27</ref> \n* '''u''' {{Note|Rav_Bib_u}} See Sinclair's commentary in \"Introduction\" in ''F\u00e9lix Ravaisson: Selected Essays''.<ref name=\"SinclairI-18\">\"Sinclair (2016), p. 18</ref>\n* '''v''' {{Note|Rav_Bib_v}} This article was one of several that appeared under the heading \"Dessin\"; the volume was edited by Ferdinand Buisson.<ref name=\"SinclairI-vi\">\"Sinclair (2016), p. vi</ref><ref name=\"SinclairI-12\">\"Sinclair (2016), p. 12</ref>\n* '''w''' {{Note|Rav_Bib_w}} See Sinclair's commentary in \"Introduction\" in ''F\u00e9lix Ravaisson: Selected Essays''.<ref name=\"SinclairI-11-12\">\"Sinclair (2016), pp. 11-12</ref>\n* '''x''' {{Note|Rav_Bib_x}} See Sinclair's commentary in \"Introduction\" in ''F\u00e9lix Ravaisson: Selected Essays''.<ref name=\"SinclairI-19-20\">\"Sinclair (2016), pp. 19-20</ref>\n* '''y''' {{Note|Rav_Bib_y}} See Sinclair's commentary in \"Introduction\" in ''F\u00e9lix Ravaisson: Selected Essays''.<ref name=\"SinclairI-18-19\">\"Sinclair (2016), pp. 18-19</ref>\n* '''z''' {{Note|Rav_Bib_z}} The second of two versions, the first edition was published in 1871, and was subsequently reworked in this much later publication. See Sinclair's commentary in \"Introduction\" in ''F\u00e9lix Ravaisson: Selected Essays''.<ref name=\"SinclairI-15-18\">\"Sinclair (2016), pp. 15-18</ref>\n* '''aa''' {{Note|Rav_Bib_aa}} The translation here is only part of the original article, the third and final section (pp. 188-256).<ref name=\"SinclairI-vi\">\"Sinclair (2016), p. vi</ref> \n|}\n\n==References==\n'''General: Primary'''\n{{refbegin}}\n*'''Sinclair, Mark'''. ''Being Inclined: F\u00e9lix Ravaisson\u2019s Philosophy of Habit'' (Oxford: Oxford University Press, 2019)\n{{refend}}\n\n\n'''General: Secondary'''\n{{refbegin}}\n*'''Carlisle, Clare'''. \"Between Freedom and Necessity: F\u00e9lix Ravaisson on Habit and the Moral Life\", in ''Inquiry'' (43/2: 2010), pp. 123\u201345\n*'''Carlisle, Clare and Mark Sinclair'''. \"Editors\u2019 Introduction\" and \"Editors\u2019 Commentary\" in F\u00e9lix Ravaisson ''Of Habit'', translation, introduction, and commentary by Clare Carlisle and Mark Sinclair (London/New York: Continuum, 2008), pp. 1-21; 78-114 \n*'''Grosz, Elizabeth'''